  1. With K=1 the conclusion would be Green because the nearest neighbor is observation 5.
  2. With K=3 the conclusion would be Green because the nearest neighbors are observations 2, 4, and 5 so the majority decision is Green.
  3. The best value for K in a highly non-linear Bayes decision boundary would be a smaller value because it could better account for the variablity in the boundary created. The more sample observations you take into account the more dilluted your decision could become.

  1. Displacement and acceleration appear to have a negative relationship, as displacement increases acceleration decreases. Horsepower and year do not appear to be related. 
## [1] -0.4163615

Weight and cylinders seem to have a positive relationship. As weight increases, the number of cylinders increase. 

## [1] 0.8975273

Mpg and year have a fairly moderate positive relationship. As mpg increases the car is probably more recent.

  1. Horsepower, displacement, and weight seem to be the best predictors of gas mileage. They show the strongest relationships in the plots agains other variables as shown below. Cylinders may also play a role in predicting mpg.
  1. There are 506 rows and 14 columns. Columns represent crime rates, residential zones, non-retail business space, Charles River dummy variable, nitrogen oxide concentration, number of rooms per building, proportion of owner-occupied units built before 1940, mean distances to employment centers, accessibility to highways, property tax rate, pupil teacher ratio, proportion of blacks, percent of lower status, median value of owner-occupied homes. The rows represent different suburbs of Boston.

There is a weak negative nonlinear relationship between crime rates and median house value. There is no clear relationship between median house value and property tax rates. There is a slight negative relationship between non-retail business space and residential zones. There is no clear relationship between proportion of blacks and percent of lower status. There is a positive nonlinear relationship between nitrogen oxide levels and older houses.

  1. There may be some relationship between per capita crime rates and the distance to employment centers. As the distance to these centers decreases crime rates increase. In relation to median house values, the lower the value the more crime rates increase.
